>Description:
Go to a Help Desk page w/ an external link, like a
  mailto link.  Click on it.  You get a popup asking
  whether to view it in Help Desk or view it in an
  external browser.  There is no "Cancel" option.
  The most likely candidate, clicking on the cancel
  box, seems to mean "view in Help Desk".  If the link
  was a mailto link, you then get an error saying that
  Help Desk doesn't know how to handle it (integration
  of SirMail can only be a matter of time...!).

I think it would be helpful to give the user a chance
  to back out.  I also think clicking on the X box
  should behave as "Cancel".
